Smart Unit Converter

A fast, single-screen Android unit converter built with Jetpack Compose.
The app focuses on speed, simplicity, and intelligent input parsing, allowing users to convert units quickly without navigating multiple screens.

Overview

Smart Unit Converter provides conversions across many measurement categories with a minimal UI and smart input handling.

Key design principles:

Single screen interaction

Fast unit switching

Smart parsing of pasted values (e.g. 12 km, 5mph)

Nearby conversion suggestions

Favorites for frequently used conversions

Educational fun facts

Features
Core Conversion

Supports multiple measurement categories including:

Length

Weight / Mass

Area

Volume

Speed

Temperature

Duration

Pressure

Angle

Energy

Power

Density

Frequency

Fuel Economy

Astronomy

Each category defines its units and conversion factors.

Smart Input Parsing

The converter accepts inputs such as:

12 km
5mph
-40 C
12kms

The parser extracts:

value
unit symbol

and automatically selects the correct From Unit.

Negative Value Handling

Negative values are allowed only for categories where they make sense.

Allowed:

Temperature

Angle

Not allowed:

Length

Weight

Volume

Pressure

Energy

Power

Density

Frequency

Fuel economy

Astronomy

Duration

Input validation is dynamically controlled by the category.

Nearby Conversion Suggestions

For a given input value, nearby values are generated to help users explore quick conversions.

Example:

Input: 100 km

Nearby values:
80 km
90 km
110 km
120 km

The step size scales automatically with the order of magnitude of the value.

Favorites

Users can store up to 6 favorite conversions for quick access.

Examples:

km → miles
kg → lb
C → F

Favorites are stored locally.

Fun Facts

For certain categories (currently length), the app displays contextual fun facts.

Example:

Did you know?
Mount Everest is about 8848 meters tall.

These references are implemented using:

ReferenceItem
ReferenceEngine
LengthReferences
Clipboard Friendly Input

Users can paste values directly from other apps:

12 km
5mph
-40 C

The parser automatically resolves unit aliases such as:

km
kms
kilometer
kilometers
Architecture

The project follows a simple MVVM structure.

UI Layer (Jetpack Compose)

Handles rendering and user interaction.

Typical components:

CategoryGrid
UnitDropdown
ResultCard
ConverterScreen

Responsibilities:

Display categories

Unit selection

Input handling

Display results

Show nearby conversions

Display fun facts

ViewModel Layer
ConverterViewModel

Responsibilities:

Conversion logic

Input parsing

Validation

Managing UI state

Favorites management

Nearby value generation

Data Layer

Handles repositories and unit storage.

FavoritesRepository
UnitRepository

Responsibilities:

Category definitions

Unit lookup

Favorite storage

Model Layer
UnitItem

Represents a unit.

Example:

UnitItem(
    name = "Kilometer",
    symbol = "km",
    factor = 1000.0
)
UnitCategory

Represents a group of units.

Example:

UnitCategory(
    name = "Length",
    units = [...]
)

Includes a flag:

allowNegative

which controls input validation rules.

Unit Categories

Categories are defined separately for modularity.

Examples:

LengthCategory
WeightCategory
TemperatureCategory
SpeedCategory
EnergyCategory
PowerCategory
DensityCategory
FrequencyCategory
FuelEconomyCategory
AstronomyCategory

Each category defines:

Unit names

Symbols

Conversion factors

Input Parsing

Parsing uses regular expressions.

Supported formats:

12 km
12kms
5mph
-40 C

The parser extracts:

numeric value
unit alias

Aliases are resolved through a mapping table.

Recent Bug Fixes
Negative Temperature Support

Temperature conversions now correctly support negative values:

-40 C
-273.15 C
Unit Parsing Fix

Inputs such as:

12kms
5mph

are now correctly parsed.

Nearby Value Generation Fix

Nearby value generation now works correctly with negative values.

Adaptive Launcher Icon Fix

Resolved launcher icon issues by regenerating the icon using Android Studio's Image Asset tool, ensuring proper adaptive icon behavior.

Project Structure
app
 ├ data
 ├ model
 ├ repository
 │   └ categories
 ├ reference
 ├ ui
 │   └ theme
 ├ util
 └ viewmodel
Future Improvements

Planned improvements include smarter parsing and additional convenience features.

Natural Language Conversion

Allow input like:

12 km to miles

The parser will automatically detect both source and destination units.

Compound Unit Parsing

Support inputs such as:

5 ft 3 in
6'2"

Useful for height conversions.

Clipboard Detection

Detect convertible values from clipboard when the app opens.

Example:

Clipboard detected: 12 km
Tap to convert
More Reference Comparisons

Add contextual comparisons for other categories such as:

Speed

Astronomy

Energy

